#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn52.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga "
msgstr "1. In Private "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Bāḷhagilānasutta → gilānasuttaṃ (bj) | bāḷhagilāyaṃ or gihīnayo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Bāḷhagilānasutta "
msgstr "10. Gravely Ill "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn52.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati andhavanasmiṃ ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Dark Forest. And he was sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "sn52.10:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Anuruddha, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.1"
msgid "“Katamenāyasmato anuruddhassa vihārena viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti? "
msgstr "“What meditation does Venerable Anuruddha practice so that physical pain doesn’t occupy his mind?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.2"
msgid "“Catūsu kho me, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, I meditate with my mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind. "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.3"
msgid "Katamesu catūsu? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.4"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi … pe … "
msgstr "I meditate observing an aspect of the body … "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.5"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "feelings … "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.6"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.7"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.8"
msgid "imesu kho me, āvuso, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti. "
msgstr "I meditate with my mind firmly established in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.10"
msgid "Rahogatavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.303, sc3
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.1"
msgid "Rahogatena dve vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.2"
msgid "sutanu kaṇḍakī tayo; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.3"
msgid "Taṇhākkhayasalaḷāgāraṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.4"
msgid "ambapāli ca gilānanti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
